  "deep_dive": {
    "full_text": "Confirmed facts: Indian equities closed marginally higher as financials, banks, PSU banks and insurance stocks advanced, while IT declined after IBM's weak outlook. Smallcaps rose about 0.7% and midcaps about 0.3%, with 11 of 16 major sectors advancing. India VIX eased to about 13.27. June CPI inflation was 4.38%, while an approximately 18% monsoon deficit was cited as a macro risk. Brent traded near $85.5 as U.S.-Iran hostilities escalated. Softer U.S. inflation supported global equities and lowered immediate Fed tightening fears, while the U.S. 10-year yield stayed near 4.58%-4.59%. Reasoned interpretation: The market's late fade shows weak conviction. Financial earnings can support selective upside, but sustained high crude threatens the rupee, imported inflation, margins and RBI flexibility. The next move depends heavily on geopolitical developments, oil, financial-sector earnings and U.S. inflation data.",
